

Build a full-stack AI-powered animated video creator  Users type prompts to generate scenes made of animated SVG drawings, with support for audio tracks, video overlays, and text. The browser is for editing and preview. Export happens server-side via WebVideoCreator and FFmpeg producing real MP4s.

---

## STACK

Frontend: Next.js 14 (App Router) + TypeScript + Tailwind
Backend: Node.js Express server (separate process, port 3001)
Rendering: web-video-creator (npm: web-video-creator) — MIT/Apache, commercial-safe
AI: Anthropic Claude API (claude-sonnet-4-20250514) for SVG scene generation
Audio: user-uploaded mp3/wav or openai, heygen, gemnei, elleven labs, TTS API for voiceover
Video: user-uploaded mp4 as background layer under SVG drawings
Storage: local filesystem for MVP (./renders/, ./uploads/, ./scenes/)

---

## CORE CONCEPT

Each "scene" is a self-contained HTML page that plays animated SVG drawings
using stroke-dashoffset pen-draw effects. Scenes can also contain:
- A background video layer (<video> element behind SVG)
- An audio track (voiceover or music, <audio> element)
- Text overlays (animated in via CSS)

During preview: scenes render live in an iframe in the browser.
During export: the Node server uses WebVideoCreator to headlessly capture
each scene as a video, then FFmpeg stitches all scenes into one MP4.

---

## PROJECT STRUCTURE

inkframe/
├── app/                          # Next.js frontend
│   ├── page.tsx                  # Main editor UI
│   ├── api/
│   │   ├── generate/route.ts     # Streams Claude SVG response
│   │   └── export/route.ts       # Triggers render server
├── render-server/                # Separate Node.js Express server
