## FRONTEND UI LAYOUT

Dark theme. Three-panel layout:

### LEFT PANEL — Scene List (280px wide)
- List of scene cards, each showing:
  - Thumbnail (rasterized iframe snapshot via html2canvas)
  - Scene number + prompt snippet (truncated to 2 lines)
  - Duration badge (e.g. "8s")
  - Layer icons: SVG (always), video camera if has video, music note if has audio
  - Right-click context menu: Duplicate, Delete, Move Up/Down
- Drag to reorder (use @dnd-kit/core)
- "＋ New Scene" button at bottom — opens prompt modal
- Global Style panel below scene list:
  - Color palette (4 hex swatches, editable)
  - Stroke width slider (1–5)
  - Font selector (Caveat / DM Mono / Georgia / monospace)
  - Scene duration slider (3s–20s)

### CENTER PANEL — Preview Player
- 16:9 iframe preview of the selected scene (800px wide)
- Scene renders live — iframe src points to /public/scenes/{id}.html
- Playback bar below iframe:
  - Play / Pause button
  - Scrub bar showing progress across ALL scenes with scene boundary markers
  - Current time / total time
  - Scene label at current position
- Below scrub bar: mini timeline strip showing all scenes in order as colored blocks

### RIGHT PANEL — Scene Editor (320px wide)
- Tabs: [Prompt] [Layers] [Settings]

**Prompt tab:**
- Large textarea: "Describe this scene..."
- Enhance button (rewrites prompt to be more visually descriptive using Claude)
- Generate button → calls /api/generate → streams SVG into scene
- Regenerate button (replaces existing SVG)
- While generating: show animated pen cursor with "drawing..." text
- Scene context toggle: "Continue from previous scene" (sends prev scene summary)

**Layers tab:**
- SVG Layer (always present, cannot remove):
  - Shows token count / element count of current SVG
  - "Edit SVG" button opens a code editor modal (Monaco or textarea)
- Video Layer (optional):
  - Toggle to enable
  - Upload mp4 or paste URL
  - Opacity slider (0–100%)
  - Z-order: behind SVG (always)
  - Trim: start time / end time within the video file
- Audio Layer (optional):
  - Toggle to enable
  - Upload mp3/wav OR click "Generate Voiceover" (calls ElevenLabs with scene prompt as script)
  - Volume slider
  - Fade in / fade out toggles (0.5s ease)
  - Start offset (delay audio by N seconds into scene)
- Text Overlays (array, add multiple):
  - Text content input
  - Font, size, color pickers
  - Position: x/y as % of canvas
  - Animation: fade-in, slide-up, typewriter
  - Appear at: Ns into scene

**Settings tab:**
- Scene name (custom label)
- Duration override
- Transition to next scene: None / Crossfade / Wipe Left / Wipe Right (0.5s)
- Background color (default #fffef9)

---

## SCENE HTML FORMAT

Each scene is a self-contained HTML file written to /public/scenes/{id}.html.
This file is what WebVideoCreator loads during export.
Structure:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <style>
    * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }
    body { width: 1920px; height: 1080px; overflow: hidden; background: {bgColor}; }
    
    /* Video layer */
    #video-layer {
      position: absolute; inset: 0;
      opacity: {videoOpacity};
      z-index: 1;
    }
    #video-layer video { width: 100%; height: 100%; object-fit: cover; }
    
    /* SVG layer */
    #svg-layer {
      position: absolute; inset: 0;
      z-index: 2;
    }
    
    /* Text overlays */
    .text-overlay {
      position: absolute;
      z-index: 3;
      opacity: 0;
    }
    
    /* Stroke animation classes */
    .stroke {
      fill: none;
      stroke-linecap: round;
      stroke-linejoin: round;
      stroke-dasharray: var(--len, 1000);
      stroke-dashoffset: var(--len, 1000);
      animation: draw var(--dur, 1s) ease-in-out var(--delay, 0s) forwards;
    }
    .fadein {
      opacity: 0;
      animation: pop var(--dur, 0.4s) ease var(--delay, 0s) forwards;
    }
    @keyframes draw { to { stroke-dashoffset: 0; } }
    @keyframes pop  { to { opacity: 1; } }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <!-- VIDEO LAYER (optional) -->
  <div id="video-layer" style="display:{hasVideo ? 'block' : 'none'}">
    <video src="{videoSrc}" muted playsinline></video>
  </div>

  <!-- SVG LAYER — AI generated -->
  <div id="svg-layer">
    {svgContent}
  </div>

  <!-- AUDIO (optional) -->
  {hasAudio ? `<audio src="${audioSrc}" id="scene-audio"></audio>` : ''}

  <!-- TEXT OVERLAYS (optional) -->
  {textOverlays.map(t => `
    <div class="text-overlay" style="left:${t.x}%;top:${t.y}%;font-family:${t.font};
         font-size:${t.size}px;color:${t.color};
         animation:${t.animation} ${t.duration}s ease ${t.delay}s forwards">
      ${t.content}
    </div>
  `).join('')}

  <script>
    // Auto-start video and audio when page loads (WVC will control timing)
    document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', () => {
      const video = document.querySelector('video');
      const audio = document.getElementById('scene-audio');
      if (video) {
        video.currentTime = {videoTrimStart};
        video.play();
      }
      if (audio) {
        setTimeout(() => audio.play(), {audioStartOffset} * 1000);
      }
    });
  </script>
</body>
</html>


When a scene is updated (new SVG, new audio, new video), regenerate this file
and write it to /public/scenes/{id}.html. The iframe in the browser previews it
live. The render server loads this same file via WVC.

CLAUDE SVG GENERATION
POST /api/generate streams a Claude response.
System prompt (inject style vars):

You are an SVG animation artist for a video creator tool called Inkframe.
Generate a single <svg> element with viewBox="0 0 1920 1080" that draws itself
using CSS animations.

STRICT RULES:
- Output ONLY the raw <svg>...</svg> element. No markdown. No explanation.
- Use ONLY these colors: {palette[0]}, {palette[1]}, {palette[2]}, {palette[3]}
- Default stroke-width: {strokeWidth}
- Default font: {font}
- All lines/paths must animate using stroke-dasharray/stroke-dashoffset with
  class="stroke" and CSS variables --len (path length) and --delay (start delay)
- All filled shapes/text must use class="fadein" for opacity reveal
- Total animation must complete within {duration} seconds
- Stagger delays so elements draw sequentially, not all at once
- Use stroke-linecap="round" and stroke-linejoin="round" on all paths
- For text: use <text> elements with class="fadein", font-family="{font}"
- Include comments labeling each visual section (e.g. <!-- title -->)
- Make it visually rich: use labels, arrows, annotations where appropriate

Previous scene summary (for continuity): {previousSummary || "none"}
Canvas: 1920x1080px


User message: the scene prompt.
Stream the response token by token. As SVG tokens stream in, inject them
directly into the iframe’s #svg-layer div using innerHTML so the user
watches it draw live as Claude responds.
After generation completes:
	1.	Extract a one-line summary from Claude (second API call, fast) for context chaining
	2.	Write the full scene HTML to /public/scenes/{id}.html
	3.	Capture a thumbnail via html2canvas on the iframe content
	4.	Update scene state

RENDER SERVER (render-server/index.js)
Express server on port 3001. Single endpoint:
POST /render
Body: { scenes: SceneObject[], outputName: string }
Logic in renderer.js:

import WebVideoCreator, { VIDEO_ENCODER } from "web-video-creator";

export async function renderScenes(scenes, outputDir) {
  const wvc = new WebVideoCreator();
  wvc.config({
    mp4Encoder: VIDEO_ENCODER.CPU.H264, // fallback, works everywhere
    browserHeadless: true,
    browserUseGPU: false, // safer for cloud Linux
    debug: false,
  });

  const videoPaths = [];

  for (const scene of scenes) {
    const outputPath = path.join(outputDir, `scene-${scene.id}.mp4`);
    
    const video = wvc.createSingleVideo({
      // Serve the scene HTML from Next.js public folder
      url: `http://localhost:3000/scenes/${scene.id}.html`,
      width: 1920,
      height: 1080,
      fps: 30,
      duration: scene.duration * 1000, // ms
      outputPath,
      // Audio is embedded in the HTML via <audio> tag, WVC captures it
    });

    await new Promise((resolve, reject) => {
      video.on("progress", (p) => {
        // Send SSE progress update to frontend
        console.log(`Scene ${scene.id}: ${p.toFixed(0)}%`);
      });
      video.on("completed", resolve);
      video.on("error", reject);
      video.start();
    });

    videoPaths.push(outputPath);
  }

  return videoPaths;
}


After all scenes render, stitch.js runs FFmpeg concat:

import ffmpeg from "fluent-ffmpeg";

export async function stitchScenes(videoPaths, transitions, outputPath) {
  // Build FFmpeg concat with optional crossfade transitions
  // For simple concat (no transitions): use concat demuxer
  // For crossfade: use xfade filter between consecutive clips
  
  const command = ffmpeg();
  videoPaths.forEach(p => command.input(p));
  
  if (transitions.every(t => t.type === "none")) {
    // Simple concat
    command
      .on("end", resolve)
      .on("error", reject)
      .mergeToFile(outputPath);
  } else {
    // Build xfade filter chain
    // xfade=transition=fade:duration=0.5:offset={sceneEndTime - 0.5}
    // Chain them: [0][1]xfade=...[v01]; [v01][2]xfade=...[v012]; etc.
    buildXfadeChain(command, videoPaths, transitions, outputPath);
  }
}


Export endpoint streams progress back to frontend via SSE:

data: {"type":"scene_progress","scene":1,"progress":45}
data: {"type":"scene_done","scene":1}
data: {"type":"stitching"}
data: {"type":"complete","downloadUrl":"/renders/output.mp4"}


STATE MANAGEMENT
Single Zustand store (useVideoStore):

interface Scene {
  id: string
  prompt: string
  summary: string
  svgContent: string
  duration: number
  bgColor: string
  thumbnail: string | null
  
  // Video layer
  videoLayer: {
    enabled: boolean
    src: string | null        // URL or /uploads/filename
    opacity: number           // 0-1
    trimStart: number         // seconds
    trimEnd: number | null
  }
  
  // Audio layer
  audioLayer: {
    enabled: boolean
    src: string | null
    volume: number            // 0-1
    fadeIn: boolean
    fadeOut: boolean
    startOffset: number       // seconds
  }
  
  // Text overlays
  textOverlays: TextOverlay[]
  
  // Transition to next scene
  transition: "none" | "crossfade" | "wipe-left" | "wipe-right"
}

interface VideoStore {
  scenes: Scene[]
  selectedSceneId: string | null
  globalStyle: GlobalStyle
  isGenerating: boolean
  isExporting: boolean
  exportProgress: ExportProgress | null
  
  // Actions
  addScene: (prompt: string) => void
  updateScene: (id: string, updates: Partial<Scene>) => void
  deleteScene: (id: string) => void
  reorderScenes: (fromIndex: number, toIndex: number) => void
  generateSVG: (sceneId: string) => Promise<void>
  exportVideo: () => Promise<string>
}


